ech. Weaknesses: difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric, not willing to further education. No extra teamwork strengths.\n\nD: strengths: responds to unexpected events adequately, can concentrate very well, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously. Weaknesses: regarded as arrogant, relatively weak leadership skills, hot temper, know-it-all. No extra teamwork strengths.\n\nNow evaluate criteria:\n\nReliability/responsibility: C (100% reliable), D (takes responsibility seriously), B (conscientious), A (anticipates dangerous situations, leadership). So C highest.\n\nTechnical/cognitive competence: A (spatial vision, complex connections), B (weather assessment, computer), C (understands complicated tech), D (problem solving, concentration). All decent.\n\nCalmness/pressure: B (handles stress), C (keeps calm in crisis), D (responds adequately), A unknown.\n\nDecision-making: C (quick correct decisions), A (anticipates dangerous), D (solves problems), B (weather assessment). All.\n\nTeamwork/communication: C creates positive atmosphere but difficulty communicating, egocentric; B grumpy/uncooperative; D weak leadership, arrogant; A leadership but poor at criticism, unfriendly.\n\nProfessional development: B computer skills, maybe good; C not willing to further education; D weak leadership; A not open to new ideas.\n\nThus B's main drawback is interpersonal; C's drawback is communication difficulty and egocentric, plus lack of development. Which is more severe? For long-distance flights, crew communication is critical. C's difficulty communicating ideas could be a safety risk. B's grumpiness/uncooperativeness also risk but maybe less severe? Hard to know.\n\nGiven the group currently leaning B, but we must consider if any new info could shift. No new strengths for C or D. So B still seems best.\n\nWe should state provisional preference Candidate B, confidence maybe 60% as before. Mention uncertainties: severity of B's interpersonal issues vs C's communication issues. Also note that A's health and organization issues are concerning.\n\nThus produce public message."}
